    "what_description": "Pleopeltis accedens is a species of epiphytic fern in the family Polypodiaceae. It has a rhizome that is creeping and scaly, with fronds that are ovate-lanceolate in shape and have a length of up to 1.5 meters. The rachis and midrib are dark brown to black, while the pinnae are pinnately arranged and have a length of up to 20 centimeters. The plant is native to the tropical regions of Central and South America, typically growing in shaded and humid environments. The fronds of Pleopeltis accedens are leathery and dark green in color, with a wavy or lobed margin.",
